# Makefile — Expected Structure

Every project MUST have a `Makefile` at the root with the commands below.

## Environment Variables

All configurable values (ports, service URLs, images, etc.) MUST be read from the `.env` file with a fallback to `.env.example` values.

```makefile
include .env
export

# Application URLs (derived from PORT variables from .env)
APP_URL ?= http://localhost:$(APP_PORT)
ADMIN_URL ?= http://localhost:$(ADMIN_PORT)
API_URL ?= http://localhost:$(API_PORT)
DB_STUDIO_URL ?= http://localhost:$(DB_STUDIO_PORT)
REDIS_URL ?= redis://localhost:$(REDIS_PORT)
PROMETHEUS_URL ?= http://localhost:$(PROMETHEUS_PORT)
GRAFANA_URL ?= http://localhost:$(GRAFANA_PORT)
PGADMIN_URL ?= http://localhost:$(PGADMIN_PORT)
SENTRY_URL ?= http://localhost:$(SENTRY_PORT)
KIBANA_URL ?= http://localhost:$(KIBANA_PORT)

# Fallback .env.example values (if .env is missing)
APP_PORT ?= 3000
ADMIN_PORT ?= 3001
API_PORT ?= 8080
DB_STUDIO_PORT ?= 5555
REDIS_PORT ?= 6379
PROMETHEUS_PORT ?= 9090
GRAFANA_PORT ?= 3000
PGADMIN_PORT ?= 5050
SENTRY_PORT ?= 8000
KIBANA_PORT ?= 5601
```

## Mandatory Commands

### `up` — Start the project (EXAMPLE TEMPLATE)

```makefile
up:
	docker compose up -d --build
	@echo ""
	@echo "🚀 Services started successfully!"
	@echo ""
	@echo "Visit the following services (Cmd/Ctrl+Click to open URLs):"
	@echo ""
	@echo "┌──────────────────────────────┬────────────────────┐"
	@echo "│ Service                          │ URL                   │"
	@echo "├──────────────────────────────┼────────────────────┤"
	@echo "│ App                              │ $(APP_URL)            │"
	@echo "│ Admin Dashboard                  │ $(ADMIN_URL)          │"
	@echo "│ API Docs                         │ $(API_URL)            │"
	@echo "│ Database Studio                  │ $(DB_STUDIO_URL)      │"
	@echo "│ Redis Commander                  │ $(REDIS_URL)          │"
	@echo "│ Prometheus                       │ $(PROMETHEUS_URL)     │"
	@echo "│ Grafana                          │ $(GRAFANA_URL)        │"
	@echo "│ PgAdmin                          │ $(PGADMIN_URL)        │"
	@echo "│ Kibana                           │ $(KIBANA_URL)         │"
	@echo "└──────────────────────────────┴────────────────────┘"
	@echo ""
	@echo "💡 Cmd/Ctrl+Click to open in browser"
	@echo ""
	@echo "To stop: make down (or press Ctrl+C)"
	@echo ""
```

### `down` — Stop the project

```makefile
down:
	docker compose down
```

### `test` — Full test suite

Run tests for EVERY app/package in the monorepo. Distinguish test types:

```makefile
test: test-unit test-integration test-e2e

test-unit:
	docker compose exec <service> npm run test:unit
	# Repeat for each app/package

test-integration:
	docker compose exec <service> npm run test:integration

test-e2e:
	docker compose exec <service> npm run test:e2e
```

If the project is not a monorepo, adapt with a single target per type.

### `coverage` — Coverage report

Run the coverage check for EVERY app/package individually:

```makefile
coverage:
	docker compose exec <service-1> npm run test:coverage
	docker compose exec <service-2> npm run test:coverage
	# One line per app/package
```

## Conditional Commands (if applicable)

### `setup` — Idempotent initialization

Run once. Must be idempotent (re-running does not break anything).

```makefile
setup:
	cp -n .env.example .env || true
	docker compose build
	$(MAKE) db-migrate
	# Other initializations (seed, etc.)
```

### `db-*` — Database operations

```makefile
db-migrate:
	docker compose exec <service> npx prisma migrate deploy

db-reset:
	docker compose exec <service> npx prisma migrate reset --force

db-seed:
	docker compose exec <service> npx prisma db seed

db-studio:
	docker compose exec <service> npx prisma studio
```

Adapt `db-*` commands to the ORM/migration tool used (Prisma, Drizzle, TypeORM, Alembic, etc.).

## Rules

- **NEVER hardcode values** — always `$(VARIABLE)` with `?=` fallback
- **ALWAYS execute via Docker** — no direct commands on the host
- **One target per test type** — `test-unit`, `test-integration`, `test-e2e`
- **One coverage target per app/package** — or a loop over packages
- **`setup` MUST be idempotent** — use `cp -n`, `|| true`, existence checks
- **`.PHONY`** — declare all targets as PHONY

```makefile
.PHONY: up down setup test test-unit test-integration test-e2e coverage db-migrate db-reset db-seed db-studio
```
